AWS proprietary technology, managed serverless NoSQL database, millisecond latency
Capacity modes: provisioned capacity with optional auto-scaling or on-demand capcity
Can replace ElastiCache as a key/value store (store session + ttl)
Highly available, multi AZ by default, read and writes are decoupled, transaction capability
DAX cluster for read cache, microsecond read latency
Security, authentication, and authorization is done through IAM
Even proccessing: DynamoDB streams to integrate with AWS Lambda, or kinesis data streams
Global Table feature: active-active replication
Automated backups to 35 days with (PITR), Or on-demand backups
Export to S3 without using RCU within thge PITR window, import from S3 without using WCU
Great to rapidly evolve schema <---- KNOW
Use cases: Serverless applications development (files around 100KB), distributed serverless cache
